{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}} – a stylized hand, with bent wrist/forearm (hence the hook stroke at lower right). Earlier forms resemble {{zh-l|*手}}, {{zh-l|*寸}}. The original meaning of the glyph was “elbow”, which is now written {{och-l|肘}}.

After the meaning “elbow” was forgotten, {{lang|zh|九}} was taken to symbolize a [[fist]] tightening to [[bump up]] against something; thus, there is a metaphorical [[bumping]] up of [[nine]] against [[ten]], which is the last number when counting on one's fingers.

